<br>
As alot of you have noticed, I'm in the process of implementing the &quot;new&quot; rules for the dragon and venril rotations and they should be complete this tuesday, the 16th of January.  While I'm at it, I'm going to be doing a few things to make my job and yours as raid leaders a little easier.<br>
<br>
FIRST of all, you'll be seeing a new forum crop up in the dragon raids section that will be called something like &quot;Rotation Lists.&quot;  That forum will be simply for my personal housekeeping to make my job easier.  It will contain the master copies of ALL FOUR of the rotation lists for the ubermobs we kill on a regular basis.<br>
<br>
Additionally, when you want to be added (or removed) from one of the four existing rotation lists in the future, you'll place your request in that forum.  The reason for this is to keep all those signup requests in the same spot so that I can easily see who's on how many lists so that I can bring oversights to everyone's attention.<br>
<br>
SECOND:  After the 16th and beginning with the next spawn for each of the ubermobs, I'll be putting a post in each of the ubermob sections everytime someone new is up for the monster.  It will look something like this:<br>
<br>
(Header) Legion of Heroes -- You're up for TRAK<br>
(Body)  Deadline: 11:59pm 1/23/01<br>
<br>
These posts will all be locked so that they aren't confused with sign up posts, but the information as to exactly when the deadline for mob dismissal comes will be available to everyone.<br>
<br>
THIRD:  There have been several requests for a POG forum and debates as to the status of the plane of growth.  To wit, is it reservable?  Can more than one &quot;raid&quot; do the plane at a time?  etc. etc.  Although I hate to create more forums, I'm beginning to come around to the idea that maybe we need a POG forum.  However, before I open one up, I'd like us to decide exactly what we want to do about POG.  There's a thread in this forum concerning the plane started by me.  Please post your thoughts there.  After a few days of consensus, I'll post up something for a vote on the issue and we'll get that proverbial ball rolling.<br>
<br>
Additionally, once we get POG issues decided, I'll probably be including it on the calendar in the future.<br>
<br>
You can post your thoughts on these changes here.   <p><BR>
